#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.2:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Sekhabalavagga"
msgstr "1. Powers of a Trainee"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: sekhabalavitthatasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Vitthatasutta"
msgstr "2. In Detail"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, sekhabalāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five powers of a trainee."

msgctxt "an5.2:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.2:1.3"
msgid "Saddhābalaṃ, hirībalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ."
msgstr "The powers of faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, saddhābalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of faith?"

msgctxt "an5.2:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "an5.2:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an5.2:2.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saddhābalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of faith."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, hirībalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of conscience?"

msgctxt "an5.2:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako hirīmā hoti, hirīyati kāyaduccaritena "
"vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, hirīyati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samāpattiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple has a conscience. They’re conscientious about bad "
"conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and conscientious about having any "
"bad, unskillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.2:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, hirībalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of conscience."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, ottappabalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of prudence?"

msgctxt "an5.2:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ottappī hoti, ottappati kāyaduccaritena "
"vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, ottappati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samāpattiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple is prudent. They’re prudent when it comes to bad "
"conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and prudent when it comes to "
"acquiring any bad, unskillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.2:4.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ottappabalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of prudence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, vīriyabalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of energy?"

msgctxt "an5.2:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful "
"qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly "
"vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.2:5.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vīriyabalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, paññābalaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the power of wisdom?"

msgctxt "an5.2:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "an5.2:6.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paññābalaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the power of wisdom."

msgctxt "an5.2:6.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca sekhabalāni."
msgstr "These are the five powers of a trainee."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.2:7.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an5.2:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘saddhābalena samannāgatā bhavissāma sekhabalena, hirībalena … ottappabalena "
"… vīriyabalena … paññābalena samannāgatā bhavissāma sekhabalenā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will have the trainee’s powers of faith, conscience, prudence, energy, "
"and wisdom.’"

msgctxt "an5.2:7.3"
msgid "Evañhi kho, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.2:7.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
